longing for sea change odile and odette longing for sea change odile and odette facebook twitter email print add to calendar this is the third video installation in the series entitled longing for sea change presented in the gallery for african art in this video odile and odette two ballerinas identically dressed in colorful batik printed tutus face each other on a dark stage their synchronized movements within a gilded frame create the illusion of a mirrored figure in this clever twist on tchaikovsky's ballet swan lake british born nigerian artist yinka shonibare mbe questions stereotypical african and western identities in today's transnational world presenting a series of video works by contemporary artists living and working in africa and its diasporas continuing through june 26 2011 the video installations are on continuous view in the center's expanded gallery for african art when ongoing every day from june 16 2010 through january 9 2011 11 00 am where cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags film arts contact 723 4177 admission open wed sun 11am 5pm thursdays until 8pm admission is free closed monday and tuesday permalink http events stanford edu events 210 21023 more info last modified november 9 2010
